<refnamediv><refname>immad</refname><refpurpose>Measure median absolute deviation.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>value = immad(image)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input image or numeric array.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>value</term><listitem><para>Median absolute deviation of all values.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Returns the median absolute deviation around the median intensity, a robust measure of image variation.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_smarties.png"));
image = imresize(image, [64 96]);
gray = rgb2gray(image);
value = immad(gray);
disp(value);
imshow(image);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
